Package: RSurvivEHR
Type: Package
Title: Survival Analysis on Electronic Health Records via SurvivEHR
Version: 0.7.3
Authors@R: person(given = "Pedro", family = "Cardoso", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "p.cardoso@exeter.ac.uk", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Description: An R interface to SurvivEHR, a transformer-based survival model
    for longitudinal Electronic Health Record (EHR) data. Build a vocabulary
    from clinical event sequences, pre-train a competing-risk or single-risk
    survival model, fine-tune on labelled outcomes, and predict time-to-event
    probabilities, all from plain R data frames. The Python backend (vendored
    inside the package) is managed automatically via 'reticulate'; no
    FastEHR installation is required.
